SIMPLE: holdfast
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Holdfast
<hw>Hold"fast`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Something used to secure and hold in place something else, as a
long flat-headed nail, a catch a hook, a clinch, a clamp, etc.; hence, a
support.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧His <xex>holdfast</xex> was gone.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Bp. Montagu.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A conical or branching body, by
which a seaweed is attached to its support, and differing from a root in
that it is not specially absorbent of moisture.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Holding</ent>⟦br⟧
